Account Manager OCD-1412835W
DESCRIPTION
Account Manager
Ortho Clinical Diagnostics
Headquartered in Raritan, NJ, with manufacturing operations in
Rochester NY, Pompano Beach, FL and Cardiff, Wales, Ortho Clinical
Diagnostics has more than 2,500 employees worldwide. We are dedicated
to investing significant resources to continuously improve our
products and develop solutions to address unmet medical needs. Our
single focus is to help hospitals, laboratories and blood centers
worldwide deliver results that help patients experience a better
quality of life.
Ortho Clinical Diagnostics serves the transfusion medicine community
and laboratories around the world. We?re a leading provider of total
solutions for screening, diagnosing, monitoring and confirming
diseases early, before they put lives at risk.
Job Description:
The Account Manager will be responsible for achieving OCD product
sales to new and established specialty accounts to achieve sales
objectives and greater market penetration.
QUALIFICATIONS
- Min. Bachelor Degree from any discipline, preferably MBA
- Interested in the Pathology Clinics or Transfusion Medicine
industry.
- Proficient in written and conversational English.
- Ability to learn in a fast-pace environment and deliver business
results.
- Constant focus toward the well being of patients, and the
satisfaction of doctors and nurses who use the product
LOCATION
This position is based in Jakarta. There is no relocation support.
How to apply
Do you meet the requirements of this position and are interested in
building a career with Johnson & Johnson? Go to www.careers.jnj.com,
select the appropriate fields under ?Search Jobs? and apply using
requisition number 1412835W by 30th April 2014. All applications must
come through the portal.
